I added a macOS-friendly, VSCode-like custom title bar with correct drag/no-drag regions per Electron v37.

What I changed:
- Main process: enabled `titleBarOverlay` on macOS with height 40 to allow a transparent overlay for custom title bar UI under the traffic lights.
- Global styles: added `.win-drag`, `.win-no-drag`, and `.titlebar-h` utilities for systematic draggable areas and consistent height.
- Title bar component: implemented `WindowTitlebar` with a draggable header, a left spacer for macOS traffic lights, and a right “no-drag” actions area.

How to use:
- The component already renders in `App.tsx`. You can add interactive buttons inside the right container; they are wrapped with `win-no-drag` to stay clickable.
- Keep interactive elements in “no-drag” containers; everything else in the header remains draggable.

Notes:
- The window uses `titleBarStyle: 'hiddenInset'` and overlay height 40; the left spacer is `72px`, which aligns well with macOS traffic lights inset.
- The overlay is transparent; the header’s backdrop and border style provide the VSCode-like feel.

Summary:
- Enabled `titleBarOverlay` in `src/main/index.ts` with height 40
- Added `.win-drag`, `.win-no-drag`, `.titlebar-h` to `src/renderer/src/styles/main.css`
- Implemented `WindowTitlebar` in `src/renderer/src/components/layout/window-titlebar.tsx` with proper drag regions and macOS spacing
- Typecheck and lint are clean